  "notes": "Unstack array along axis into tuple of arrays (NumPy 2.x). Cost: numel(output).",
  "notes_sections": [
    "``unstack`` serves as the reverse operation of :py:func:`stack`, i.e., ``stack(unstack(x, axis=axis), axis=axis) == x``.",
    "This function is equivalent to ``tuple(fnp.moveaxis(x, axis, 0))``, since iterating on an array iterates along the first axis."
  ],
